  "original_title": "\u2019\u0ba8\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b85\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0b9a\u0bbf \u0ba4\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bc1 \u0b8f\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0baa\u0b9f\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bc1\u2019",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "'There will be no shortage of rice in the country'",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Ministry of Trade and Food Security has said that there will be no shortage of rice in the country.",
        "According to the Secretary to the Ministry SD Kodikara, 47 thousand metric tons of rice has been imported during the period up to the 25th.",
        "He also mentioned that 25,000 metric tons of rice has been imported this month alone.",
        "He pointed out that the said amount of rice has been imported under the India Loan Scheme.",
        "In this situation, the Ministry of Commerce and Food Security has further informed that the rice distribution operation has been suspended due to the fuel crisis. (a)"
      ],
